						<summary>

						<p>This is built in in the middle and is incomplete towards the end. It records a gift of sheep for burning a lamp (in the temple) by a lady named Dēvaṉ Śōlai residing at Rāyaśikhāmaṇi a quarter of Rājarāja-chaturvēdimaṅgalam (Ambāsamudram) a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Muḷḷi-nāḍu a division of Rājarāja-maṇḍalam.</p>						

						</summary>
